fOvrX pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-33_ pf-text-1"><b>Raising awareness</b> - World Sight Day highlights the global prevalence of blindness and vision impairment, encouraging conversations and education about eye health. By raising awareness, learners gain a deeper understanding of the challenges faced by millions worldwide and the importance of preventive measures.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-35_ pf-text-1"><b>Prevention and early detection</b> - Early detection is critical to preventing vision loss. Through initiatives such as screenings and educational campaigns, World Sight Day encourages individuals to prioritise their eye health and seek regular check-ups. Learners are empowered to know the importance of timely intervention and access to eye care services.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-37_ pf-text-1"><b>Advocacy and action</b> - World Sight Day mobilises governments, organisations, and individuals to advocate for policies and programs that support vision care. By engaging in advocacy efforts, learners actively drive change and promote equitable access to eye care for all.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-39_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Sight_Day_A_Comprehensive_Guide_to_Vision_Health_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_2.jpg?v=1710757934" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Sight_Day_A_Comprehensive_Guide_to_Vision_Health_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_2.jpg?v=1710757934 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Sight_Day_A_Comprehensive_Guide_to_Vision_Health_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_-_2_1000x.jpg?v=1710757934 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/World_Sight_Day_A_Co